headlines.description: — Cam Thomas scored a career-high 44 points off the bench and the short-handed Brooklyn Nets rallied from a 23-point deficit to stun the Washington Wizards 125-123 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas helps Nets rally from 23 down to beat Wizards 125-123

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — When LeBron James was pulling up his dribble to float an alley-oop pass to Anthony Davis, or diving into the stands in an attempt to regain the ball for the Lakers, he appeared far more concerned with immediate team goals than making NBA history.
headlines.shortLinkText: James closes on NBA scoring record, Lakers fall to Pelicans

headlines.description: — Deandre Ayton had 31 points and 16 rebounds to help the Phoenix Suns beat the Detroit Pistons 116-100 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayton has 31 points and 16 rebounds, Suns beat Pistons

events.name: LA Clippers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 35 points, Paul George added 30 and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the New York Knicks 134-128 in overtime Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard has 35 points, Clippers outlast Knicks 134-128 in OT

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — The Chicago Bulls tried all sorts of defensive coverages on Damian Lillard. He kept scoring anyway.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zach LaVine scores 36 as Bulls beat Trail Blazers 129-121

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had a triple-double with 35 points, 15 rebounds and 11 assists and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the short-handed Miami Heat 123-115 on Saturday night for their seventh straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo has triple-double; Bucks win 7th straight

events.name: Houston Rockets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — The Oklahoma City Thunder took what coach Mark Daigneault called a "bloodthirsty mentality" into Saturday's rematch with the Houston Rockets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 42 as Thunder blow out Rockets

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry went down and the Golden Warriors once again had to fight like crazy to close out a game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry injures left leg leading Warriors over Mavs 119-113

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored a season-high 41 points, Nikola Jokic had his 18th triple-double of the season and the Denver Nuggets won their third straight game, beating the Atlanta Hawks 128-108 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets beat Hawks 128-108, tie Boston for NBA's best record
